		{
			"img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
			"name": "Pressure Point Attack",
			"sort": 800000,
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "action"
				},
				"actions": {
					"value": 2
				},
				"category": "offensive",
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>Hakusa targets a foe's pressure points to debilitate them. Hakusa makes a fist Strike. On a hit, the target takes damage as normal and must attempt a @Check[fortitude|dc:35] save. Regardless of the result of the save, the target is temporarily immune to Pressure Point Attack for 1 minute.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> The target's muscles become temporarily weaker. For 1 round, the target is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeebled 2} and must succeed at a @Check[flat|dc:5] check when attempting to use actions with the manipulate trait or the action is lost.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> As success, but the duration is 1 minute.</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As success, but the duration is 1 minute, the flat check is @Check[flat|dc:11], and the target also takes -10-foot status penalty to their Speed for the duration.</p><p>@UUID[Item.6NzhqF7DOCyc84OF]{Effect: Pressure Point Attack (Success)}</p><p>@UUID[Item.fJkU0HTMFYahDKks]{Effect: Pressure Point Attack (Failure)}</p><p>@UUID[Item.1TnHKZy2DL5NcOEb]{Effect: Pressure Point Attack (Critical Failure)}</p>",
